HEADWORD: airheaded
<hw>airheaded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>lacking seriousness;
given to frivolity; scatterbrained; stupid; simple-minded; <as>as,
<ex>airheaded</ex> teenagers</as>. Contrasted with <ant>serious</ant>,
<ant>solemn</ant></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dizzy, empty-headed, featherbrained, giddy,
lightheaded, light-headed, silly</syn>⟦br⟧
